This course gives an in-depth overview about the classical and contemporary theory of international trade, theory of trade policy, and their applications.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to deepen the knowledge of students about theory of international trade, theory of trade policy, and their applications.   We will use both the theories of perfectly competitive and imperfectly competitive markets, depending on particular trade models. Recent developments in the areas of trade theory and trade empirics will be discussed.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students acquire following skills and knowledge: * Knowledge of main theories of international trade, an advanced core field of economics * Skills to apply mathematical, statistical and econometric methods in analysis of international trade and trade policy * Ability to critically evaluate empirical studies in the field of international trade * Knowledge about developments in the field of international trade and application of trade policy in the world
